# Real Time

<aside class='notice'>This is an experimental feature. Do not use it in production. Specifications can change at any time.</aside>

## Websockets

The real time API uses **websockets** to push devices information in real-time and it is based on the famous <a href="http://socket.io/">socket.io</a> library. We support WSS, WebSockets over SSL/TLS, like HTTPS. We also support fallback to long polling for older browsers.

`data-received` is currently the only available topic. Everytime a device publishes data to the platform data is pushed over the channel. With the same model as <a href="/#get-a-device">device `GET`</a>.

